(ENGINEERING MINI PROJECT ABSTRACT) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PROJECT TITLE) Tj
T*
(Paws ? Pet Adoption and Pet Care Commerce Platform) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(ABSTRACT) Tj
T*
(Paws is a full-stack web application designed as an engineering mini project to digitize pet) Tj
T*
(adoption workflows, pet care operations, and basic pet product commerce in one integrated) Tj
T*
(platform. The system combines role-based user management \(user, staff, admin\), pet listing and) Tj
T*
(moderation, adoption request processing, shopping cart and order flow, medical record tracking,) Tj
T*
(and in-app notifications. The project demonstrates practical software engineering concepts) Tj
T*
(including modular API design, database schema design, authentication/authorization, and) Tj
T*
(client?server integration with a modern TypeScript-based stack.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The backend is built with Node.js + Express in TypeScript and exposes RESTful APIs for) Tj
T*
(authentication, pets, adoptions, shop, cart, orders, medical records, and notifications.) Tj
T*
(Authentication uses JWT tokens, passwords are hashed with bcrypt, and role checks enforce) Tj
T*
(access boundaries for admin/staff-only operations. The database layer uses SQLite through) Tj
T*
(`better-sqlite3`, with schema initialization and migration checks handled programmatically.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The frontend is built with React 19 + Vite + TypeScript, using React Router for client-side) Tj
T*
(routing and Tailwind CSS v4 for styling. Additional UI/UX libraries include lucide-react icons,) Tj
T*
(motion animations, and sonner toast notifications. The frontend consumes backend APIs via a) Tj
T*
(centralized API client and stores session state in local storage for persistent login behavior.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Overall, this mini project is suitable for demonstrating end-to-end product engineering from) Tj
T*
(local development to deployment packaging, while remaining compact enough for academic) Tj
T*
(evaluation and iterative feature enhancement.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(ENGINEERING PROBLEM STATEMENT) Tj
T*
(Traditional pet adoption handling in small shelters is often manual, fragmented, and difficult) Tj
T*
(to audit. The problem addressed is to provide a unified, digital system that supports:) Tj
T*
(? transparent pet listing and approval workflows,) Tj
T*
(? secure user registration and role-based operations,) Tj
T*
(? structured adoption application tracking,) Tj
T*
(? basic e-commerce for pet supplies,) Tj
T*
(? medical record follow-ups and user notifications.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(OBJECTIVES) Tj
T*
(1. Build a multi-role pet platform with secure authentication.) Tj
T*
(2. Support pet discovery and adoption application lifecycle.) Tj
T*
(3. Provide admin/staff dashboards for moderation and operations.) Tj
T*
(4. Integrate pet shop cart and order workflows.) Tj
T*
(5. Persist all core entities in a relational database.) Tj
T*
(6. Deliver a deployable, container-friendly project structure.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CORE FEATURE MODULES) Tj
T*
(? Authentication & Profile: signup, login, JWT profile access, profile updates.) Tj
T*
(? Pet Management: listing available pets, submitting pets, admin approval/rejection.) Tj
T*
(? Adoption Management: submit adoption requests, admin review and status updates.) Tj
ET
